<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
<p>St. John's Episcopal Church, established in 1963, served the area around Temperance, MI.  The Episcopal Diocese of Michigan along with Reverend C. M. Stuart and the Trinity Episcopal Church parish in Monroe, MI, founded St. John's Mission.  Bishop Archie H. Crowley held the first service on July 21, 1963, at the Temperance Library.  Land was purchased in November 1964, and on July 25, 1969, the Mission held a groundbreaking ceremony.  It was not until January 18, 1970, when the first service was held at the new church building.  During its history, the church conducted traditional services and ceremonies sanctioned by the Episcopalian faith.  In 1997, the Church closed down because of the dwindling numbers of active members.</p>
</bioghist>

<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
<p>St. John's Episcopal Church records consist of The records contain meeting minutes, photographs, financial reports, correspondence, and membership and church activity records.  The records are organized into eight series: Registers of baptisms, communicants, burials, marriages, etc.; Registers of services ; Membership records; Photographs and Background Material; Activities; Administrative Records; Bishop's Committee Meetings, and Miscellaneous.</p>
</scopecontent>

